---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Vertical Image Research"
  description="Privacy Policy for Vertical Image Research."
  showGate={false}
>
  <section class="legal-page">
    <div class="shell legal-shell">
      <p class="eyebrow">LEGAL</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="effective"><strong>Effective date:</strong> July 13, 2026</p>

      <p>This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>Vertical Image Research</strong> (the "App"), operated by <strong>Edith Jenius</strong> ("we", "us", or "our"), handles information when you use the App.</p>

      <h2>1. Information we receive</h2>
      <p>If you choose to connect your TikTok account, the App may receive only the information you explicitly authorize through TikTok's authorization flow, such as:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>basic public profile information (for example, display name, profile image, and account identifier);</li>
        <li>a list of your recent public videos and associated public metadata (for example, title, cover image, creation time, and engagement counts);</li>
        <li>a temporary authorization token needed to maintain the connection.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>The App does <strong>not</strong> collect your TikTok password. The App does not request private messages, contacts, precise location, payment data, or data from other users' accounts.</p>

      <h2>2. How we use information</h2>
      <p>We use authorized information only to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>authenticate your connection to TikTok;</li>
        <li>display your own authorized public profile and video information in the dashboard;</li>
        <li>operate, secure, troubleshoot, and improve the App;</li>
        <li>comply with legal obligations and applicable platform requirements.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do not sell personal information. We do not use authorized TikTok data for targeted advertising, and we do not use it to train machine-learning models.</p>

      <h2>3. Sharing</h2>
      <p>We do not share authorized TikTok data with third parties except when necessary to provide the App, comply with law, protect rights and security, or with your direction or consent.</p>
      <p>TikTok processes information according to its own privacy policy and terms when you use its authorization flow or services.</p>

      <h2>4. Retention and security</h2>
      <p>We keep information only for as long as needed to operate the App, meet legal obligations, resolve disputes, or enforce agreements. We use reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect information. No internet-based service can guarantee absolute security.</p>

      <h2>5. Your choices and deletion requests</h2>
      <p>You can stop using the App at any time. You may revoke the App's access through TikTok's account settings where available.</p>
      <p>To request deletion of information associated with the App, email <strong>jeniusedith@gmail.com</strong> with the subject line <strong>"Vertical Image Research data deletion request"</strong>. We will verify the request where appropriate and delete applicable information within a reasonable period, unless retention is required by law or necessary for security, fraud prevention, or dispute resolution.</p>

      <h2>6. International transfers</h2>
      <p>Information may be processed in locations where we or service providers operate. Where required, we use appropriate safeguards for such transfers.</p>

      <h2>7. Children</h2>
      <p>The App is not directed to children and is not intended for anyone who cannot lawfully use TikTok or consent to these terms. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.</p>

      <h2>8. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will post the updated version on this page and revise the effective date.</p>

      <h2>9. Contact</h2>
      <p>For privacy questions or requests, contact: <strong>jeniusedith@gmail.com</strong>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page { padding: 74px 0 20px; }
  .legal-shell { max-width: 820px; }
  h1 { margin: 0 0 18px; font-family: Georgia, "Noto Serif SC", serif; font-size: clamp(44px, 6vw, 68px); font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.08; }
  .effective { margin: 0 0 34px; color: var(--muted); }
  p, li { color: var(--muted); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.85; }
  p { margin: 0 0 18px; }
  h2 { margin: 42px 0 12px; font-family: Georgia, "Noto Serif SC", serif; font-size: 26px; font-weight: 500; }
  ul { margin: 0 0 20px 20px; padding: 0; }
  strong { color: var(--ink); }
</style>
